      <h3><b>The Okinawan Karate Club of Madison</b></h3>
      <h4><b>Martial arts training for adults and mature teens</b></h4>
      <p>
        <b>The Okinawan Karate Club of Madison</b> teaches traditional Okinawan Shorin Ryu
        karate as taught by <%= link_to "Eizo Shimabukuro O'Sensei", 
        "http://www.usadojo.com/biographies/eizo-shimabukuro.htm" %> and Okinawan Shudokan
        karate as taught by the late <%= link_to "Walter Todd Sensei",
        "http://www.koryu.com/library/mskoss10.html" %>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Complete karate training:</b>
          <ul>
            <li>Kata/forms</li>
            <li>self-defense</li>
            <li>Okinawan weapons (kobudo)</li>
            <li>overall fitness and conditioning</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
      <p>
        There are many benefits to karate training. As a dedicated student you can
        <ul>
          <li>improve strength and indurance</li>
          <li>develop better posture</li>
          <li>enhance focus and self discipline</li>
          <li>build confidence</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <i>Classes starting soon!</i> If you would like more information on about training
        please send email to <a href = "&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#111;&#107;&#99;&#109;&#97;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#111;&#110;&#64;&#103;&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#46;&#99;&#111;&#109;">
        &#111;&#107;&#99;&#109;&#97;&#100;&#105;&#115;&#111;&#110;&#64;&#103;&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#46;&#99;&#111;&#109;</a>.
